---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle="About — Thibaut LEFRANCOIS" title="About">
  <div
    class="text-sage-11 flex max-w-prose flex-col gap-5 text-base leading-relaxed md:gap-6"
  >
    <p>
      I'm Thibaut, a full-stack developer based in France with a strong pull
      toward the creative side of the web. I like building things that feel as
      good as they work, whether that means crafting smooth animations, thinking
      through an architecture, or getting the details right on a UI.
    </p>
    <p>
      I studied computer science at IUT La Rochelle, where I completed a
      three-year BUT Informatique with a full-stack specialization. During that
      time, I joined
      <a
        href="https://www.raccourci.fr"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-sage-12 underline"
        >Raccourci Agency<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a
      >
      as an apprentice, first on back-end work and then across the full stack.
      I'm still there today, contributing to architecture decisions, mentoring,
      code reviews, and sprint planning alongside development.
    </p>
    <p>
      In 2025, I started freelancing under my own structure, Arko, and enrolled
      in a master's-level program at OpenClassrooms to earn the RNCP level 7
      title in software development. Around the same time, I took Bruno Simon's
      <a
        href="https://threejs-journey.com"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-sage-12 underline"
        >Three.js Journey<span class="sr-only"> (opens in new tab)</span></a
      >
      course, which opened the door to WebGL and creative development. That's
      where most of my current energy goes: exploring what's possible when code
      meets visual expression.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a
        href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l69ztiHjXb1Q0WuAgiSPmeoh-eoq8Ep9/view?usp=sharing"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="text-sage-12 underline"
        >View my resume &rarr;<span class="sr-only">
          (opens in new tab)</span
        ></a
      >
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
